lines: The Brume's our home, and we'll take good care of it!
We won't get up to no mischief while you're gone. Not too much, anyway!
We'll change Ishgard into a country we can all be proud of! Just you watch!
You can hardly call us a proper watch when we ain't got no uniforms or trainin'. That'll all come with time, though, I hope.
Gibrillont's takin' donations from folk for buildin' new homes. Ain't been long and we've already got a respectable sum, would you believe that?
More'n a few of our folk were at Falcon's Nest, hopin' to be a part of history...only to come back callin' for that damned wyrm's head. <sigh>
Let them dragons come! We've been trainin' for this!
Seems we both lived through this one, eh?
Ever since all this new blood's joined the watch, Symme's been actin' a bit odd. Like he's eager to prove himself, or somethin'...
For years we've been spittin' curses at the bluebloods from the shadows of the Brume, but at long last we've found ourselves a place in the sun. I'm glad I chose to throw my lot in with the Mongrel.
Bah, I can't believe we let that bastard get away. Feels like the mission ain't truly over till we catch him, but maybe that's just me.
If Rostnsthal hadn't pointed it out, I never even would've guessed there was someone else pullin' the strings. I s'pose we're still new to this investigatin' business, eh?
Hilda says the Hounds'll be doin' some trainin' alongside the Temple Knights. Probably best that we know how the other does things so's we don't end up steppin' on each other's toes.

obj.n: As Goes Light, So Goes Darkness
The First Flight of the Excelsior
For Those We Can Yet Save
